item.contest_details:
The College Basketball Crown is a new 16-team, single-elimination postseason tournament for men's college basketball teams that didn't make the NCAA Tournament, hosted in Las Vegas by Fox Sports and Anschutz Entertainment Group. 
Here's a more detailed breakdown:
Purpose: To provide an alternative postseason opportunity for teams that didn't qualify for the NCAA Tournament (March Madness). 
Format: A 16-team, single-elimination tournament. 
Location: MGM Grand Garden Arena and T-Mobile Arena in Las Vegas. 
Timing: The tournament runs from March 31 to April 6, 2025. 
Teams:
Two automatic qualifiers from the Big East Conference, Big Ten Conference, and Big 12 Conference. 
Ten at-large teams selected from the pool of teams that did not qualify for the NCAA tournament. 
Broadcast: All games are broadcast on FOX and FS1, and streamed on FOXSports.com and the FOX Sports App. 
NIL Incentives: The championship team will receive a $300,000 NIL package, the runner-up a $100,000 package, and the semifinalists $50,000 packages. 
First-ever tournament: The 2025 College Basketball Crown is the inaugural tournament. 

--------
Nebraska Cornhuskers (20-14, 7-13 Big Ten) vs. UCF Knights (20-16, 9-14 Big 12)

Las Vegas; Sunday, 5:30 p.m. EDT

The Knights are 9-14 against Big 12 opponents and 11-2 in non-conference play. UCF ranks fifth in the Big 12 with 10.2 offensive rebounds per game led by Moustapha Thiam averaging 2.7.

The Cornhuskers are 7-13 in Big Ten play. Nebraska is fifth in the Big Ten with 24.9 defensive rebounds per game led by Berke Buyuktuncel averaging 4.1.

UCF averages 80.1 points, 7.3 more per game than the 72.8 Nebraska gives up. Nebraska has shot at a 45.6% rate from the field this season, 0.7 percentage points higher than the 44.9% shooting opponents of UCF have averaged.

TOP PERFORMERS: Keyshawn Hall is shooting 42.8% and averaging 18.8 points for the Knights. Darius Johnson is averaging 3.1 made 3-pointers over the last 10 games.

Connor Essegian averages 2.2 made 3-pointers per game for the Cornhuskers, scoring 10.4 points while shooting 37.2% from beyond the arc. Brice Williams is averaging 22.7 points over the last 10 games.

LAST 10 GAMES: Knights: 7-3, averaging 83.1 points, 35.4 rebounds, 14.0 assists, 7.8 steals and 4.7 blocks per game while shooting 44.2% from the field. Their opponents have averaged 80.2 points per game.

Cornhuskers: 4-6, averaging 75.4 points, 30.9 rebounds, 14.0 assists, 6.6 steals and 2.9 blocks per game while shooting 44.3% from the field. Their opponents have averaged 76.7 points.
item.side1_details: UCF's only ranked win this season came in November when they topped Texas A&M 64-61. However, they faced tough competition in the Big 12 with 91-87 loss to Kansas and another overtime loss to Kansas to finish the season. They also lost a close game to Houston 69-68 after leading Houston by 8 at half time. Houston is currently playing in the NCAA national championship game.
item.side2_details: Nebraska missed the NCAA tournament despite having 4 wins over ranked teams throughout the the season, including wins over Creighton (14), UCLA (15), Illinois (18) and Oregon (16). Their ranked losses were to Michigan (15), Maryland (25), Wisconsin (18), and Purdue (20).
